    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "5093096b_6c7f0821",
        "filename": "src/chromiumos/tast/ssh/exec.go",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 335,
      "author": {
        "id": 1118346
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-04-28T07:15:52Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Ah, I failed to notice that signature of DumpLogOnError is different between testexec and ssh. I assume it\u0027s because this package can\u0027t depend on chromiumos/tast/testing, right?\n\nI hope we can use the same signature for the two packages. Can we avoid circular imports by introducing some internal packages for example?",
      "parentUuid": "1561af8d_0225a135",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 335,
        "startChar": 14,
        "endLine": 335,
        "endChar": 21
      },
      "revId": "ed5209a2209ac7341a4e01575c81cd52c0fddad7",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "7029f19b_2ae454cf",
        "filename": "src/chromiumos/tast/ssh/exec.go",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 335,
      "author": {
        "id": 1150179
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-04-28T08:12:00Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "That\u0027s right, as DumpLogOnError\u0027s TODO comment.\n\nIf ssh depends on testing, we have the following cyclic deps\n\npackage chromiumos/tast/bundle\n        imports chromiumos/tast/dut\n        imports chromiumos/tast/internal/linuxssh\n        imports chromiumos/tast/ssh\n        imports chromiumos/tast/testing\n        imports chromiumos/tast/dut",
      "parentUuid": "5093096b_6c7f0821",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 335,
        "startChar": 14,
        "endLine": 335,
        "endChar": 21
      },
      "revId": "ed5209a2209ac7341a4e01575c81cd52c0fddad7",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "95ef6689_cf79298c",
        "filename": "src/chromiumos/tast/ssh/exec.go",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 335,
      "author": {
        "id": 1150179
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-04-28T08:29:51Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "testing -\u003e dut (s.DUT() *dut.DUT) is hard to break, as it\u0027s used from tests.\ndut -\u003e ssh (d.Conn() *ssh.Conn) is hard to break.\nssh -\u003e testing (testing.ContextLog) might be breakable. Let me look into it.",
      "parentUuid": "7029f19b_2ae454cf",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 335,
        "startChar": 14,
        "endLine": 335,
        "endChar": 21
      },
      "revId": "ed5209a2209ac7341a4e01575c81cd52c0fddad7",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "280d36ee_f37107a5",
        "filename": "src/chromiumos/tast/ssh/exec.go",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 335,
      "author": {
        "id": 1118346
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-04-28T08:46:09Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think the key problems are:\n- The ssh package is for both framework and tests\n- The testing package is for tests only\n- testing.ContextLog is the only way today to emit logs via context.Context\n\nMy recommendation is to introduce a common way for framework and tests to emit logs via context.Context, e.g. chromiumos/tast/internal/logging.",
      "parentUuid": "95ef6689_cf79298c",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 335,
        "startChar": 14,
        "endLine": 335,
        "endChar": 21
      },
      "revId": "ed5209a2209ac7341a4e01575c81cd52c0fddad7",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "ae4f4876_b00f761c",
        "filename": "src/chromiumos/tast/ssh/exec.go",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 335,
      "author": {
        "id": 1150179
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-04-28T10:28:00Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I confirmed we can fix cyclic imports by moving some methods and structs from tast/testing to tast/internal/testing. https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromiumos/platform/tast/+/2169537\nWDYT?\n\nHaving a common way sounds nice, but also like a lot of work. What about leaving TODO in internal/testing and refactor it later?",
      "parentUuid": "280d36ee_f37107a5",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 335,
        "startChar": 14,
        "endLine": 335,
        "endChar": 21
      },
      "revId": "ed5209a2209ac7341a4e01575c81cd52c0fddad7",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "50ad9d1b_c3aaeb1c",
        "filename": "src/chromiumos/tast/ssh/exec.go",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 335,
      "author": {
        "id": 1118346
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-04-30T10:24:58Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Hmm. I\u0027m a bit hesitant because we have to change the signature of the public API later.\n\nAlso I\u0027m afraid that people might pass *testing.State around unnecessarily just to pass s.Log to DumpLogOnError. To use testing.ContextLog we need a boilerplate:\n\n ssh.Run(..., ssh.DumpLogOnError(func(args ...interface{}) {\n   testing.ContextLog(ctx, args...)\n }))",
      "parentUuid": "ae4f4876_b00f761c",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 335,
        "startChar": 14,
        "endLine": 335,
        "endChar": 21
      },
      "revId": "ed5209a2209ac7341a4e01575c81cd52c0fddad7",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
